text.section:
Exposure to HIV between a victim and a person charged with a prohibited exposure occurs:
by percutaneous or mucocutaneous contact with blood or body fluids;
by contact for a prolonged period with blood or body fluids of an open wound, including dermatitis, exudative lesions, and chapped skin;
by intact skin contact for a prolonged period with large amounts of blood or body fluids; or
under any other condition or circumstance under which a person may be exposed to HIV.
